name: Activated charcoal
description: Activated charcoal is a fine, odorless, and tasteless black powder made from coal, wood, peat, coconut shell, or petroleum coke. It is treated with oxygen to open up millions of tiny pores that capture and trap toxins and chemicals in the body.

name: Acupuncture
description: Acupuncture is a form of traditional Chinese medicine that involves inserting thin needles into specific points on the body. It is believed to help balance the flow of energy, or qi, within the body.

name: Alfalfa
description: Alfalfa is a plant that is commonly used as a dietary supplement due to its high nutritional content. It belongs to the legume family and has a long history of use in traditional medicine.

name: Aloe vera
description: Aloe vera is a succulent plant that has thick, fleshy leaves containing a gel-like substance. It has been used for centuries for its medicinal properties and is known for its soothing and healing benefits.

name: Anise (Pimpinella anisum)
description: Anise is a flowering plant in the Apiaceae family, native to the eastern Mediterranean region and Southwest Asia. The seeds are used as a spice and for their medicinal properties.

name: Apple cider vinegar
description: Apple cider vinegar is made from fermented apple juice. It is known for its acidic properties and has been used for centuries for its health benefits.

name: Arnica
description: Arnica is a perennial herb found in mountain areas of Europe and North America. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its anti-inflammatory and pain-relieving properties.

name: Aromatherapy
description: Aromatherapy is a holistic healing treatment that uses essential oils extracted from plants to promote physical, emotional, and mental well-being. The oils can be inhaled, applied topically, or used in a diffuser to create a therapeutic atmosphere.

name: Ashwagandha
description: Ashwagandha is an herb commonly used in traditional Indian Ayurvedic medicine for its adaptogenic properties, which help the body cope with stress and anxiety. It is also known for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects.
alternateNames: Withania somnifera, Winter cherry, Indian ginseng

name: Astragalus
description: Astragalus is a plant native to China and has been used in Traditional Chinese Medicine for centuries. The root of the plant is typically dried and used in herbal remedies.

name: Barberry
description: Barberry is a shrub that is native to Europe, northern Africa, and western Asia. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine due to its various therapeutic properties.

name: Basil
description: Basil is a fragrant herb commonly used in cooking, but it also has many medicinal properties. It belongs to the mint family and is known for its strong aroma and flavor.

name: Bee Pollen
description: Bee pollen is a mixture of flower pollen, nectar, enzymes, honey, and wax collected by bees as a protein source. It is considered a superfood due to its high nutritional content.

name: Bilberry
description: Bilberry is a small, dark blue fruit that is similar in appearance to a blueberry. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for various ailments.

name: Black cohosh
description: Black cohosh is a herb native to North America that has been traditionally used for its medicinal properties. It is commonly used to treat symptoms of menopause and menstrual disorders.

name: Blue vervain
description: Blue vervain is a perennial herb that is native to North America. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Borage oil
description: Borage oil is extracted from the seeds of the borage plant, also known as starflower. It is rich in gamma-linolenic acid (GLA), an omega-6 fatty acid that the body needs for various functions.

name: Buchu
description: Buchu is a plant native to South Africa and has been used for centuries by the indigenous people for medicinal purposes. The leaves of the Buchu plant are dried and used to make teas and extracts.

name: Burdock root
description: Burdock root is a plant that is native to Europe and Asia. It has been used in traditional medicine for centuries due to its potential health benefits.

name: Butterbur
description: Butterbur is a plant native to Europe and parts of Asia, commonly used in herbal medicine for its potential health benefits.

name: Calendula cream
description: Calendula cream is a topical ointment made from the Calendula officinalis plant, also known as marigold. It is commonly used for its anti-inflammatory and healing properties.

name: Cayenne pepper
description: Cayenne pepper is a type of chili pepper commonly used in cooking and for its medicinal properties. It is high in capsaicin, which is responsible for its spicy taste and many health benefits.

name: Celery seed extract
description: Celery seed extract is derived from the seeds of the Apium graveolens plant, commonly known as celery. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Chamomile tea
description: Chamomile tea is a herbal tea made from the dried flowers of the chamomile plant. It has a mild, soothing taste and is commonly consumed for its calming and relaxing properties.

name: Chlorella supplements
description: Chlorella supplements are derived from a type of freshwater algae that are rich in nutrients and antioxidants. They are commonly available in tablet or powder form and are often used as a dietary supplement.

name: Clove Oil
description: Clove oil is derived from the clove plant, specifically the buds of the Syzygium aromaticum tree. It has a warm, spicy aroma and is commonly used in aromatherapy and traditional medicine practices.

name: Colloidal silver
description: Colloidal silver is a supplement consisting of microscopic silver particles suspended in liquid. It is believed to have natural antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties.

name: Comfrey ointment
description: Comfrey ointment is a natural remedy made from the Comfrey plant, known for its healing properties. The ointment is made by extracting the mucilage and allantoin from the Comfrey plant and combining it with a carrier oil or beeswax.

name: Cranberry juice
description: Cranberry juice is a popular fruit juice made from cranberries, known for its tart flavor and vibrant red color. It is often consumed for its potential health benefits, particularly for urinary tract health.

name: Cucumber slices
description: Cucumber slices have long been used as a natural remedy for various skin and health conditions. They are known for their cooling and hydrating properties.

name: DGL (Deglycyrrhizinated licorice)
description: DGL is a form of licorice root that has been processed to remove the compound glycyrrhizin, which can cause side effects such as high blood pressure when consumed in large amounts. DGL is commonly used as a supplement to help with digestive issues and inflammation.

name: DMSO (Dimethyl sulfoxide)
description: DMSO is a colorless liquid that is used topically to reduce pain and inflammation. It works by reducing swelling, improving blood flow, and blocking pain signals in the body.

name: Damiana
description: Damiana is a plant native to Central and South America that has been traditionally used for its medicinal properties. The leaves of the plant are harvested and used in various forms, such as tea or supplements.

name: Dandelion Tea
description: Dandelion tea is an herbal tea made from the roots or leaves of the dandelion plant. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Dead Sea salts
description: Dead Sea salts are mineral-rich salts that are extracted from the Dead Sea, a saltwater lake located between Jordan and Israel. These salts have been used for centuries for their wellness and beauty benefits.

name: Devil's claw
description: Devil's claw is a plant native to southern Africa that has been used for centuries as a natural remedy for various health conditions.

name: Dill oil
description: Dill oil is derived from the seeds or leaves of the dill plant through steam distillation. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Dong quai
description: Dong quai is a traditional Chinese herb that has been used for centuries in herbal medicine. It is known for its potential health benefits, particularly for women's health.

name: Dr. Bach's Rescue Remedy
description: Dr. Bach's Rescue Remedy is a blend of five flower essences created by Dr. Edward Bach, a British physician and homeopath. This natural remedy is designed to provide relief during times of stress, anxiety, or emotional upheaval.

name: Dragon's blood
description: Dragon's blood is a bright red resin that is derived from a variety of different plants, including the Croton, Dracaena, Daemonorops, and Pterocarpus species. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine practices in South America, Africa, and Asia.

name: Echinacea
description: Echinacea is a flowering plant native to North America that has been used medicinally for centuries. It is commonly used to boost the immune system and treat various infections.

name: Elderberry
description: Elderberry is a fruit from the elder tree that has been used for centuries for its medicinal properties. The berries are commonly used to make syrup, tea, and other remedies.

name: Eleuthero (Siberian ginseng)
description: Eleuthero is an adaptogenic herb that has been used in traditional Chinese medicine and Russian traditional medicine for centuries due to its potential health benefits.

name: Elm bark
description: Elm bark comes from the inner bark of the elm tree and has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Enzyme supplements
description: Enzyme supplements are natural substances that help break down food into smaller, more easily absorbable nutrients. They are often taken to aid digestion for those who have difficulty breaking down food due to various health conditions.

name: Epsom salt
description: Epsom salt is a naturally occurring mineral compound of magnesium and sulfate. It is named after the town of Epsom in England, where it was originally discovered.

name: Essential fatty acids
description: Essential fatty acids are a type of polyunsaturated fats that are important for overall health and well-being. The body cannot produce them on its own, so they must be obtained through diet or supplementation.

name: Eucalyptus oil
description: Eucalyptus oil is derived from the leaves of the eucalyptus tree and is known for its fresh, invigorating aroma. It has been used for centuries for its medicinal properties.

name: Evening primrose oil
description: Evening primrose oil is derived from the seeds of the evening primrose plant, which is native to North America. It is rich in omega-6 fatty acids, particularly gamma-linolenic acid (GLA).

name: Eyebright
description: Eyebright is a small flowering plant that has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its beneficial properties for the eyes.

name: Fennel Tea
description: Fennel tea is an herbal tea made from the seeds of the fennel plant, Foeniculum vulgare. It has a slightly sweet and aromatic flavor.

name: Fennel seeds
description: Fennel seeds are commonly used in cooking as a flavoring agent, but they also have medicinal properties. These small, oval seeds have a sweet and licorice-like flavor.

name: Fenugreek
description: Fenugreek is an herb commonly used in cooking and traditional medicine. It has a long history of use in various cultures for its medicinal properties.

name: Feverfew
description: Feverfew is a flowering plant that belongs to the daisy family. It is native to Europe and has been used as a medicinal herb for centuries.

name: Fig leaf tea
description: Fig leaf tea is made by steeping dried fig leaves in hot water. Fig leaves are known for their medicinal properties and have been used in natural remedies for various health conditions.

name: Fish oil
description: Fish oil is a dietary supplement that contains omega-3 fatty acids, which are essential nutrients that our bodies cannot produce on their own.

name: Flavanol-rich foods
description: Flavanol-rich foods are foods that contain high levels of flavanols, a type of plant compound with antioxidant properties. Some common sources of flavanols include dark chocolate, red wine, green tea, berries, apples, and citrus fruits.

name: Flaxseed oil
description: Flaxseed oil is derived from the seeds of the flax plant (Linum usitatissimum). It is rich in omega-3 fatty acids, particularly alpha-linolenic acid (ALA).

name: Frankincense
description: Frankincense is a resin obtained from the Boswellia tree and has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various healing properties.

name: Fruit-infused water
description: Fruit-infused water is made by adding fresh fruits, herbs, and sometimes vegetables to a pitcher of water and allowing it to infuse for several hours or overnight. This process imparts the water with the natural flavors and nutrients of the ingredients, resulting in a refreshing and flavorful beverage.

name: Garlic supplements
description: Garlic supplements are capsules or tablets made from concentrated extract of garlic, a popular herb known for its strong flavor and potential health benefits.

name: Gelatin supplements
description: Gelatin supplements are made from animal collagen, typically derived from bones, skin, and connective tissues. Gelatin is a protein that is rich in amino acids such as glycine and proline.

name: Ginger tea
description: Ginger tea is a herbal tea made from the rhizome of the ginger plant. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Ginseng
description: Ginseng is a popular herbal remedy that has been used in traditional Chinese medicine for centuries. It is derived from the root of the Panax ginseng plant and is believed to have various health benefits.

name: Goldenrod
description: Goldenrod is a flowering plant native to North America and Europe. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Goldenseal
description: Goldenseal is a perennial herb native to the northeastern United States and southeastern Canada. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its medicinal properties.

name: Gotu Kola
description: Gotu kola is a perennial plant native to Asia that has been used in traditional medicine for centuries. The leaves of the plant are rich in antioxidants and contain several active compounds that have beneficial effects on the body.

name: Grapefruit seed extract
description: Grapefruit seed extract is derived from the seeds and pulp of grapefruit and is known for its strong antimicrobial properties.

name: Green tea
description: Green tea is a type of tea that is made from Camellia sinensis leaves and buds that have not undergone the same withering and oxidation process used to make black tea. It is known for its numerous health benefits and is rich in antioxidants.

name: Guava leaves
description: Guava leaves have been used for centuries for their medicinal properties. They are rich in antioxidants, antibacterial, and anti-inflammatory properties, making them a popular natural remedy for various health issues.

name: Hemp oil
description: Hemp oil is derived from the hemp plant and contains high levels of cannabidiol (CBD) with very low levels of THC, the psychoactive component of marijuana. It is commonly used for medicinal purposes due to its non-intoxicating properties and potential health benefits.

name: Herbal tea
description: Herbal tea is a beverage made by steeping herbs, flowers, roots, and other plant parts in hot water. It is commonly used for its medicinal properties and soothing effects.

name: Hibiscus Tea
description: Hibiscus tea is a herbal tea made from the dried petals of the hibiscus flower, known for its tart and fruity flavor. It is often enjoyed hot or cold and can be brewed alone or mixed with other herbs or fruits.

name: Holy Basil
description: Holy basil is a plant used in traditional medicine practices, particularly in Ayurveda. It is known for its strong aromatic properties and is commonly used in culinary dishes as well.

name: Homeopathic Remedies
description: Homeopathic remedies are a natural form of medicine that uses highly diluted substances to promote healing and balance within the body. This alternative medicine practice is based on the principle that "like cures like," meaning a substance that causes symptoms in a healthy person can be used to treat similar symptoms in a sick person.

name: Honey
description: Honey is a sweet, natural substance produced by bees from the nectar of flowers. It has been used for centuries for its therapeutic properties.

name: Horseradish
description: Horseradish is a pungent root vegetable that is commonly used as a condiment in cooking. It has been used for centuries for its medicinal properties due to its high levels of antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals.

name: Horsetail
description: Horsetail is a plant that has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its medicinal properties. It is rich in silica, which is essential for healthy bones, skin, and hair.

name: Horsetail extract
description: Horsetail extract is derived from the horsetail plant, a medicinal herb that has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its health benefits.

name: Hydrogen peroxide
description: Hydrogen peroxide is a chemical compound that consists of two hydrogen and two oxygen atoms. It is a colorless liquid that is commonly used as a household disinfectant and antiseptic.

name: Hyssop
description: Hyssop is a herbaceous plant in the mint family that is native to the Mediterranean region. It has a long history of use in traditional medicine for its medicinal properties.

name: Ibuprofen
description: Ibuprofen is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) that is commonly used to reduce pain, fever, and inflammation. It works by inhibiting the production of chemicals in the body that cause pain and inflammation.

name: Ice pack
description: An ice pack is a portable plastic sac filled with cold gel or frozen water that is applied to the skin to provide relief from pain or swelling.

name: Immune-boosting supplements
description: Immune-boosting supplements are vitamins, minerals, and other substances that are taken to help strengthen the immune system and defend the body against illness and infection.

name: Indian Ginseng (Ashwagandha)
description: Indian ginseng, also known as Ashwagandha, is an ancient medicinal herb that has been used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine for centuries. It is known for its adaptogenic properties, which help the body cope with stress and anxiety.

name: Inhaler
description: An inhaler is a medical device that delivers medication directly into the lungs through the use of a handheld device. It is commonly used to treat respiratory conditions such as asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), and other lung diseases.

name: Intravenous fluids
description: Intravenous fluids are a method of administering fluids, electrolytes, medications, and nutrition directly into the bloodstream through a vein. This is typically done using a plastic catheter inserted into a vein in the hand, arm, or leg.

name: Iodine Tincture
description: Iodine tincture is a solution of iodine and potassium iodide used as a disinfectant and antiseptic.

name: Ionic Foot Detox Bath
description: An ionic foot bath is a detoxification treatment that involves immersing the feet in a basin of warm water while a device generates a low-level electrical current to create positively and negatively charged ions. These ions are said to help draw out toxins and impurities from the body through the feet.
alternateNames: Ionic foot cleanse, Ionic foot spa

name: Iron supplements
description: Iron supplements are oral medication that contain iron, a mineral essential for the production of hemoglobin, a protein in red blood cells that carries oxygen throughout the body.

name: Isopropyl alcohol
description: Isopropyl alcohol is a common disinfectant and antiseptic that is used to clean wounds and surfaces.

name: Jackfruit leaves

name: Jamaican dogwood

name: Jambul fruit

name: Japanese knotweed

name: Jasmine tea
description: Jasmine tea is a type of tea that is made by blending green or white tea leaves with jasmine flowers. The jasmine flowers are added during the tea processing to infuse the tea with a delicate floral aroma and sweet taste.

name: Jewelweed
description: Jewelweed is a plant known for its soothing properties, particularly on skin conditions such as poison ivy rashes.

name: Job's tears

name: Jojoba butter

name: Jojoba oil

name: Juniper berries

name: Kale Extract
description: Kale extract is derived from the leafy green vegetable kale, which is known for its high nutritional content. It is often used in supplement form for its various health benefits.

name: Kava Kava

name: Kelp
description: Kelp is a type of brown seaweed that is commonly found in the ocean. It is rich in essential vitamins and minerals, including iodine, potassium, calcium, and magnesium.

name: Kiwi
description: Kiwi is a small, green fruit with a fuzzy brown skin that is packed with vitamins and nutrients. It is commonly found in many parts of the world and is known for its sweet and tart taste.

name: Kombu

name: Kombucha

name: Korean Ginseng

name: Krill Oil

name: Kudzu

name: Kutki (Picrorhiza kurroa)

name: L-glutamine supplements
description: L-glutamine is an amino acid that is naturally produced in the body and plays a key role in various bodily functions. It is also available in supplement form to support overall health and well-being.

name: L-lysine supplements

name: Lavender oil

name: Lavender sachet

name: Lemon balm

name: Lemon water

name: Licorice root

name: Marshmallow root

name: Milk thistle

name: Olive leaf extract

name: Orange peel

name: Parsley leaf

name: Passionflower

name: Plantain leaf

name: Pomegranate juice

name: Primrose oil

name: Quaker Oats
description: Quaker Oats are a type of oatmeal that is made from whole grain oats. They are commonly consumed as a healthy breakfast option.

name: Quassia amara extract
description: Quassia amara extract is derived from the bark of the Quassia amara tree, native to South America. It has been used in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Quassia bark
description: Quassia bark comes from the Quassia amara tree, a small tree native to South America. It has a very bitter taste and is commonly used in herbal medicine.

name: Queen Anne's lace (Daucus carota)
description: Queen Anne's lace is a flowering plant that is commonly found throughout North America, Europe, and Asia. It has delicate white flowers that resemble lace, hence its name.

name: Quercetin supplements
description: Quercetin is a type of flavonoid antioxidant found in plants like fruits, vegetables, and grains. It is commonly taken in supplement form to provide additional health benefits.

name: Quercus alba bark
description: Quercus alba bark is the bark of the white oak tree, native to North America. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its therapeutic properties.

name: Quillaja saponaria
description: Quillaja saponaria is a tree native to South America that has been traditionally used for its medicinal properties. The inner bark of the tree contains saponins, which are natural surfactants with soap-like properties.

name: Quince fruit
description: Quince fruit is a fragrant, golden-yellow fruit that belongs to the same family as apples and pears. It has a unique flavor and is commonly used in cooking and baking.

name: Quinine
description: Quinine is a compound extracted from the bark of the cinchona tree. It has been used for centuries as a treatment for malaria and has also been used to relieve muscle cramps.

name: Quinoa
description: Quinoa is a grain-like seed that is a popular health food due to its high nutritional content. It is gluten-free and is a good source of protein, fiber, and various vitamins and minerals.

name: Raspberry leaf tea
description: Raspberry leaf tea is made from the dried leaves of the red raspberry plant. It has been used for centuries as a traditional herbal remedy for a variety of health issues.

name: Raw Honey
description: Raw honey is a natural sweet substance produced by honeybees from the nectar of plants. It is not pasteurized or processed, preserving its natural enzymes and nutrients.

name: Red clover
description: Red clover is a wild plant belonging to the legume family. It is commonly used for its medicinal properties and is often made into supplements, teas, or extracts.

name: Reishi mushroom
description: Reishi mushroom is a type of fungus that has been used in traditional Chinese medicine for centuries. It is known for its medicinal properties and is often referred to as the "mushroom of immortality".

name: Rhodiola (Rhodiola rosea)
description: Rhodiola is an herb that grows in cold regions of the world, including the Arctic and mountainous regions of Europe and Asia. It has been used in traditional medicine for centuries to help increase energy, endurance, and mental focus.

name: Rice water
description: Rice water is the starchy water left over after rice is cooked or soaked. It has been used for centuries in various cultures as a beauty treatment for skin and hair.

name: Rooibos tea
description: Rooibos tea is a herbal tea made from the leaves of the rooibos plant, native to South Africa. It has a naturally sweet taste and a reddish color when brewed.

name: Rosemary
description: Rosemary is an aromatic herb that belongs to the mint family. It is commonly used in cooking and has a strong, pine-like fragrance.

name: Rosewater
description: Rosewater is a byproduct of the distillation of rose petals to create rose essential oil. It has been used for centuries as a natural beauty product and in various cultural and religious ceremonies.

name: Rubbing alcohol
description: Rubbing alcohol is a common household product that is used as a disinfectant and antiseptic. It is made up of isopropyl alcohol which has antimicrobial properties.

name: Saffron
description: Saffron is a spice derived from the flower of Crocus sativus, which is native to Southwest Asia. It is known for its distinctive flavor, aroma, and bright yellow color.

name: Sage
description: Sage is a herb that is commonly used in cooking for its strong flavor, but it also has medicinal properties. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Saw Palmetto
description: Saw Palmetto is a plant that is commonly used as a supplement to improve prostate health. It is commonly found in North America.

name: Senna
description: Senna is an herb that is commonly used as a natural laxative to treat constipation. It contains compounds called sennosides that have a stimulating effect on the intestines.
alternateNames: Cassia senna, Alexandrian senna, Indian senna

name: Shepherd's Purse
description: Shepherd's purse is a medicinal herb that has been used for centuries for its health benefits. It is known for its small white flowers and heart-shaped seed pods.

name: Skullcap
description: Skullcap is a type of herb that belongs to the mint family. It is native to North America and has been used in traditional herbal medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Slippery Elm
description: Slippery elm is a species of elm tree native to North America. Its inner bark is harvested and processed into a thick gel-like substance that has been used medicinally for centuries.

name: Spearmint
description: Spearmint is a herb from the mint family that is commonly used for its medicinal properties as well as its culinary uses.

name: Spirulina
description: Spirulina is a type of blue-green algae that is rich in nutrients and considered a superfood. It is commonly consumed in supplement form or added to smoothies and juices.

name: St. John's Wort
description: St. John's Wort is a plant with yellow flowers that is commonly used as a medicinal herb.

name: Tea tree oil
description: Tea tree oil is an essential oil that comes from the leaves of the tea tree plant. It has been used for centuries for its various medicinal properties.

name: Thistle
description: Thistle is a flowering herbaceous plant that is commonly used for medicinal purposes. The most commonly used part of the plant is the seeds, which are known for their therapeutic properties.

name: Thyme
description: Thyme is an aromatic herb native to the Mediterranean region and commonly used in cooking and natural remedies. It has antibacterial, antifungal, and antiseptic properties.

name: Thyme tea
description: Thyme tea is an herbal tea made from the leaves of the Thymus vulgaris plant. It has been used for centuries for its medicinal properties and is known for its strong flavor and aroma.

name: Tiger Balm
description: Tiger Balm is a topical ointment that has been used for centuries in traditional Chinese medicine. It is a blend of herbal ingredients, including camphor, menthol, clove oil, and cassia oil, that work together to provide relief from aches, pains, and other discomforts.

name: Tryptophan
description: Tryptophan is an essential amino acid that is important for the production of serotonin, a neurotransmitter that regulates mood, sleep, and appetite.

name: Tulsi
description: Tulsi is an aromatic plant in the mint family that is commonly used in traditional Indian medicine. It has a strong, pungent aroma and is believed to have various health benefits.

name: Turmeric
description: Turmeric is a spice that comes from the turmeric plant. It is commonly used in Asian cuisine and is known for its bright yellow color and distinct flavor.

name: Turmeric milk
description: Turmeric milk is a traditional Ayurvedic drink made by heating milk with turmeric and other spices. It is known for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.

name: Ulluco
description: Ulluco is a tuberous root vegetable native to the Andes region of South America. It is a popular crop in countries like Peru, Bolivia, and Ecuador.

name: Ulmus Rubra (Slippery Elm)
description: Slippery elm is a species of elm tree native to North America. The inner bark of the tree is used in traditional medicine for its mucilaginous properties.

name: Umbelliferae
description: Umbelliferae is a family of flowering plants commonly known as the celery, carrot, or parsley family. It includes many well-known herbs and vegetables such as parsley, dill, cilantro, and carrots.

name: Umeboshi
description: Umeboshi is a traditional Japanese delicacy made from pickled plums that are salted and aged. They have a unique salty and tangy flavor.

name: Uncaria Tomentosa (Cat's Claw)
description: Uncaria Tomentosa, commonly known as Cat's Claw, is a medicinal plant native to the Amazon rainforest. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine to treat a variety of ailments.

name: Ursolic Acid
description: Ursolic acid is a natural compound found in various plants, such as apples, basil, rosemary, and lavender. It is known for its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and anti-cancer properties.

name: Urtica Dioica
description: Urtica Dioica is a plant commonly known as stinging nettle due to the stinging sensation caused by its tiny hairs when it comes into contact with skin. It has been used in traditional medicine for its numerous health benefits.

name: Urtication
description: Urtication involves intentionally applying a stinging nettle plant to the skin in order to produce a stinging sensation. This therapy has been used for centuries as a folk remedy for various health conditions.

name: Usnea
description: Usnea is a lichen that grows on trees and rocks and has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties.

name: Uva Ursi
description: Uva Ursi is a plant native to North America and Europe. The leaves of this plant have been used for various medicinal purposes for centuries.

name: Valerian root
description: Valerian root is a perennial herb native to Europe and Asia that has been used for centuries as a natural remedy for various ailments, particularly sleep disorders and anxiety.

name: Vanilla Bean Skin Balm
description: Vanilla bean skin balm is a natural skincare product made from infusing vanilla beans into a nourishing oil base, such as coconut oil or shea butter. The soothing aroma of vanilla adds a pleasant scent to the balm, making it a luxurious treat for dry and irritated skin.

name: Vanilla extract
description: Vanilla extract is a concentrated form of vanilla flavoring derived from vanilla beans. It is commonly used in cooking and baking to add a rich and sweet vanilla flavor to dishes.

name: Velvet bean powder
description: Velvet bean powder is derived from the seeds of the Mucuna pruriens plant, which is native to tropical regions. It has long been used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Verbena essential oil
description: Verbena essential oil is extracted from the leaves of the lemon verbena plant through steam distillation. It has a refreshing citrus scent and is often used in aromatherapy and as a natural fragrance.

name: Vervain Tea
description: Vervain tea is made from the leaves and flowers of the vervain plant, which is known for its medicinal properties. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine to promote relaxation and overall well-being.

name: Vetiver oil
description: Vetiver oil is derived from the roots of the vetiver plant, a grass native to India. It has a deep, earthy aroma and is often used in aromatherapy and as a natural remedy for various health issues.

name: Vinca minor tincture
description: Vinca minor tincture is a herbal remedy made from the plant Vinca minor, also known as periwinkle. The tincture is typically made by extracting the active compounds from the leaves and flowers of the plant using alcohol.

name: Vinegar compress
description: A vinegar compress involves soaking a cloth in vinegar and applying it to the affected area. This remedy has been used for centuries to help relieve inflammation, pain, and skin conditions.

name: Vitamin C supplements
description: Vitamin C supplements are a form of vitamins that are taken orally to increase the levels of vitamin C in the body. Vitamin C is an essential nutrient that plays a crucial role in various bodily functions.

name: Walnuts
description: Walnuts are nuts that grow on trees and are native to the Middle East and Central Asia. They are a rich source of antioxidants, omega-3 fatty acids, and other nutrients.

name: Warm compress
description: A warm compress therapy involves applying a warm, wet cloth or heating pad to a specific area of the body. The heat helps to increase blood flow, relax muscles, and reduce pain and inflammation.

name: Water therapy
description: Water therapy involves using water in various forms (such as drinking, soaking, or showering) to promote healing and overall well-being.

name: Watermelon Seed Tea
description: Watermelon seed tea is a herbal remedy made from the seeds of the watermelon fruit. These seeds are typically dried, ground, and brewed into a tea.

name: Wheatgrass juice
description: Wheatgrass juice is made from young grass of the wheat plant, typically grown indoors for around 7-10 days before being juiced. It is a potent source of vitamins, minerals, enzymes, and chlorophyll.

name: White tea
description: White tea is made from young tea leaves and buds that are harvested before they fully open. The leaves are lightly processed to preserve their natural antioxidants, resulting in a delicate and subtle flavor.

name: White willow
description: White willow is a tree native to Europe and Asia that has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its therapeutic properties. It is commonly used as an herbal remedy for pain relief and inflammation.

name: Wild Yam
description: Wild yam is a plant native to North America that has been traditionally used for its medicinal properties. The root of the wild yam plant is the part that is typically used for its health benefits.

name: Willow bark
description: Willow bark is the bark of the willow tree and has been used for centuries as a natural remedy for various ailments.

name: Witch hazel
description: Witch hazel is a plant native to North America that has been used for centuries for its medicinal properties. The leaves, bark, and twigs of the witch hazel plant are commonly used to make a natural astringent and topical remedy.

name: Xanthan gum
description: Xanthan gum is a polysaccharide that is commonly used as a food additive and thickening agent. It is produced through the fermentation of sugar by the Xanthomonas campestris bacterium.

name: Xanthium (Cocklebur)
description: Xanthium is a medicinal herb that has been used in Traditional Chinese Medicine for centuries. It is derived from the cocklebur plant, known scientifically as Xanthium strumarium.

name: Xanthones (from mangosteen)
description: Xanthones are a group of biologically active compounds found in the fruit of the mangosteen tree. They have potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, making them popular in traditional medicine and natural health remedies.

name: Xanthorrhizol (from turmeric)
description: Xanthorrhizol is a compound found in turmeric (Curcuma xanthorrhiza) with potential medicinal properties. It is known for its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial properties.

name: Xerophyte extracts
description: Xerophytes are plants that have adapted to survive in arid and dry conditions by storing water in their leaves, stems, or roots. These plants have unique properties that can be extracted and used for various health benefits.

name: Ximenia caffra (sour plum)
description: Ximenia caffra, also known as sour plum, is a tree native to Southern Africa. The fruit of the tree is commonly used for its medicinal properties.

name: Ximenynic acid
description: Ximenynic acid is a rare fatty acid that is found in the seed oils of the Ximenia americana tree. It is known for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.

name: Xylitol
description: Xylitol is a natural sugar alcohol derived from plants, often extracted from birch trees. It is commonly used as a sugar substitute in various products.

name: Xylopia aethiopica (Ethiopian pepper)
description: Xylopia aethiopica is a plant native to West Africa and is commonly used in traditional African medicine and cooking. The seeds of the plant are dried and ground into a powder for various uses.
alternateNames: Grains of Selim, Ethiopian pepper, African pepper, Uda seed

name: Xylopia frutescens
description: Xylopia frutescens is a plant native to West Africa that is commonly used in traditional medicine for its various health benefits.

name: Yarrow
description: Yarrow is a flowering plant that has been used for medicinal purposes for centuries. It is native to Europe and Asia but can now be found growing in many regions around the world.

name: Yellow Corn Silk
description: Yellow Corn Silk is the fine, thread-like strands found on ears of corn that are often discarded before cooking. However, these silk strands are actually a valuable herbal remedy with numerous health benefits.

name: Yellow Dock
description: Yellow Dock is a perennial herb that is native to Europe and western Asia. It has long, slender leaves and small yellow flowers.

name: Yellow Mustard
description: Yellow mustard is made from the seeds of the mustard plant that is commonly used as a condiment. The seeds are ground into a paste and can be used for various medicinal purposes.

name: Yerba Mate
description: Yerba mate is a traditional South American drink made by steeping the leaves of the yerba mate plant in hot water. It is known for its stimulating effects due to the presence of caffeine, theobromine, and theophylline.

name: Yerba Santa
description: Yerba Santa is a plant native to North America, specifically in the southwestern United States and Mexico. It is known for its aromatic leaves and small white flowers.

name: Ylang-Ylang
description: Ylang-Ylang is a tropical tree native to Indonesia, Malaysia, and the Philippines. It is known for its distinct floral scent and is often used in aromatherapy and skincare products.

name: Yohimbe
description: Yohimbe is an herbal supplement derived from the bark of a tree native to Africa. It has been used for centuries in traditional medicine for its potential aphrodisiac properties.

name: Yohimbine
description: Yohimbine is a chemical compound extracted from the bark of the yohimbe tree native to Africa. It is commonly used as a dietary supplement and has been studied for its potential effects on sexual health and weight loss.

name: Yucca
description: Yucca is a plant native to the deserts of the Americas, known for its medicinal properties.

name: Zaffer (Saffron)
description: Zaffer, also known as saffron, is a spice derived from the flower of Crocus sativus. It is used in cooking, baking, and traditional medicine.

name: Zedoary root
description: Zedoary root is a type of root that belongs to the ginger family. It is commonly used in traditional Asian medicine for its medicinal properties.

name: Zeolite
description: Zeolite is a naturally occurring mineral compound that is known for its ability to trap toxins and heavy metals in the body and safely eliminate them through urine and feces.

name: Zinc ointment
description: Zinc ointment is a topical medication that contains zinc oxide as its active ingredient. It is commonly used to treat a variety of skin conditions due to its soothing and protective properties.

name: Zinc supplements
description: Zinc supplements are dietary supplements that are taken to increase zinc levels in the body. Zinc is an essential mineral that plays a crucial role in various bodily functions.

name: Zingiber essential oil
description: Zingiber essential oil is derived from the root of the zingiber plant and is widely used for its medicinal properties and spicy aroma.

name: Zingiber officinale (ginger)
description: Zingiber officinale, or ginger, is a flowering plant that is widely used as a spice in cooking and as a natural remedy for various ailments. It has a pungent taste and aroma due to its bioactive compound, gingerol.

name: Zizyphus (Jujube)
description: Zizyphus is a fruit-bearing plant native to China that has been used in traditional Chinese medicine for centuries. The fruit is sweet and tangy and can be eaten fresh or dried.

name: Zone Therapy
description: Zone therapy, also known as reflexology, is a form of alternative medicine that involves applying pressure to specific points on the feet, hands, or ears to promote healing in corresponding areas of the body.

name: Zostrix (capsaicin cream)
description: Zostrix is a topical cream that contains capsaicin, the active component found in chili peppers. It works by blocking the transmission of pain signals from the skin to the brain.
